    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "One lesson is that parents can sometimes forget what selling those cookies is ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "for",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "—which implies that a) people aren’t perfect, and b) even well-meaning parents can make mistakes.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Another is that sugar is an highly-addictive, heavily-marketed substance that sells far more than healthy alternatives, despite that fact that most parents would rather their kids make healthy, wise-minded choices when they grow up.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "And a third?",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": " That monopolies thrive in a closed market—where organizations can set the price and expect little, if any, competition. That’s why GSUSA is a tax-exempt non-profit that makes ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "$800 million a year",
          "marks": [
            "link-0"
          ]
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": " on glorified bake sales (while each troop earns just 80 cents per box of cookies sold).",
          "marks": []
        }
      ],
      "markDefs": [
